134	/// A rule instance whose cells are supplied as **pre-rendered flat strings**
135	/// (BEHAVIOR.md interop, round 5). The consumer renders fact/term text with its own
136	/// printer — including any abbreviation — and this crate's wrap + escape pipeline
137	/// ([`wrap_cell`]) applies to those strings exactly as it does to a [`RuleInstance`]'s
138	/// rendered facts. `info` is the whole info-cell text (`#t : Rule[…]`); `premises`
139	/// and `conclusions` are one flat fact string per cell.
