//! WRAPPING prem/concl cell, sweep the layout width and record the [min,max]
//! band of widths that reproduce the actual cell bytes exactly. Emit
//! (n_cells, flat_i, sum_others, T, wlo, whi) so the width<->flats coupling can
//! be characterized. Ignored; run with GRAPHCLEAN_CORPUS set.

